<TITLE> Govt eliminating disparity in education: Nahid </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May29 (bdnews24.com)The government is set to eliminate discrimination in education system by launching a uniform education system at primary level, the education minister said on Friday. "We are committed to remove the disparity at primary education as there are 11 types of education systems prevalent at our primary level," Nurul Islam Nahid told a function marking the 57th anniversary of the cultural organisation 'Khelaghar' at Chhayanaut auditorium in the capital. Nahid said his ministry expected to expand technological and vocational education alongside developing higher education standards. The minister stressed the need for good and skilled teachers for the children. "We cannot afford quality teachers for the children as we fail to ensure good remuneration and due respect." On the Khelaghar, he said, "Since its inception, the Khelaghar has been working to develop the mind of the children to ensure their bright future." Khaleghor came into being on May2, 1952 with a mission for cultural development of the children. At present, there are nearly 300 Khelaghor Ashars or centres operating across the country. The chairperson of Khelaghar, Mahfuza Khanam, and secretary, Lenin Chowdhury, also spoke. b
